On average, babies say their first words between seven to 12 months of age and begin constructing coherent sentences by age two to three. But this may not be the case with Cardi B and Offset’s son, whose mother said can talk at just four months. “I’m not exaggerating, this baby is talking”, Cardi claimed in a recent Instagram video. “I put this on everything I love.” The 29-year-old American rapper went on to mention that her husband, Offset, witnessed the magical moment. - Advertisement -   TV hosts Makinwa, Isime named brand for ‘ankara’…     Yul Edochie: my 40th birthday wish is to be President     AY opens on challenges during film shoot in Miami   According to her, she asked her son if he loved her and he responded. “Yesterday, I was like ‘You love Mommy? Yeah?'”, the mother-of-two shared with her 121 million Instagram followers. “Then I asked him again, ‘You love Mommy?’ And he replied back, ‘Yeah!”‘ The awestruck rapper continued: “I don’t know if that’s like the pandemic thing. I don’t know if this is normal. “This sh’t is crazy. I need a camera in his room 24/7.” Cardi and her Migos rapper husband welcomed their second child on September 4, 2021. The superstar couple is yet to reveal his name or face, but Cardi loves to talk about him on her social media accounts.